{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"06793c0b28404c805d3290c84cfb3dd3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Tenho contexto suficiente. R-025 = consolidar D-030..D-036 em 1 doc.\n\nStack já escolhida/candidate:\n- Next 16.2.6 + Turbopack + React 19.2.4 + Tailwind 4.3\n- Prisma 7.8 + Postgres + pgvector (já instalado `postgresql-18-pgvector`)\n- @prisma/adapter-pg\n- OpenAI 6.39 (LLM client)\n- Supabase ssr + supabase-js (auth + db client)\n- Stripe 22 (payments)\n- web-push 3.6\n- zustand 5\n- Base UI 1.5\n- framer-motion 12\n- three 0.184 + @react-three/fiber + @react-three/drei (Mandala 3D?)\n- @vercel/og (open graph)\n- zod 3.25\n- bcryptjs + jsonwebtoken (auth — JWT próprio!)\n- otpauth (TOTP)\n- qrcode\n- ioredis (rate limit, queue)\n- vitest + playwright\n- @akasha/core* (5 engines já existem como packages workspace)\n- @akasha/mentor (CLI/TUI existente)\n- @akasha/types\n- @react-pdf/renderer + jspdf (export Mandala/PDF)\n- ink 5.2 (mentor CLI)\n- @supabase/storage (grimório PDF storage?)\n\nVou também verificar o uso atual — `apps/akasha-portal/src/lib/infrastructure/ritual-storage.ts` foi modificado — para entender storage. E `apps/akasha-portal/src/components/akasha/dashboard/` para entender o state.\n\nDecisões a fixar em R-025:\n1. Frontend framework: Next.js 16 (App Router) + React 19 + RSC + Turbopack — confirmed\n2. Styling: Tailwind 4 + Base UI + cva + tailwind-merge + framer-motion + tw-animate-css — confirmed\n3. State: zustand 5 (client) + RSC (server) — confirmed\n4. Forms/validation: zod 3.25 — confirmed\n5. DB: Postgres 18 + pgvector + Prisma 7.8 (config.ts) — confirmed\n6. Adapter: @prisma/adapter-pg — confirmed\n7. Auth: Supabase Auth (recomendado) + JWT próprio para compat — analisar\n8. LLM: OpenAI SDK 6.39 + AI Gateway Vercel + Minimax como modelo — analisar\n9. Realtime: SSE (HTTP stream, Edge-friendly) > WebSocket (stateful) — para Mentor chat\n10. Storage: Supabase Storage (grimório PDFs) + Vercel Blob (imagens Mandala) — analisar\n11. PWA: next-pwa ou serwist (TBD) + web-push — confirmed\n12. Test: vitest + @testing-library + playwright — confirmed\n13. E2E: Playwright (browser-driven) + Chrome DevTools MCP — confirmed\n14. i18n: next-intl (vs [lang] nativo Next 16) — confirmar com pesquisa\n15. Deploy: Vercel (Fluid Compute Node 24 LTS) vs self-host — confirmar\n16. Observability: Sentry + Vercel Analytics + Logflare/structured logs — confirmar\n17. Queue: ioredis (existe) — para Mandato scheduler + job queue (Resend/email, push)\n18. Background jobs: Vercel Queues (beta) ou BullMQ (Redis) — analisar\n19. Email: Resend (modernos) — confirmar\n20. Cron: Vercel crons (vercel.ts) — confirmar\n21. 3D: three.js + r3f (Mandala 3D) — confirmar\n22. 2D viz: D3 ou custom SVG? — pesquisar\n23. PDF: @react-pdf + jspdf (já existem) — confirmed\n24. QR: qrcode (2FA TOTP) — confirmed\n25. Secrets: Vercel env (recomendado) vs .env local\n26. CLI: ink 5.2 (mentor) — confirmed\n\nD-030 a D-036 (sub-itens de Fase 4):\n- D-030 Next.js 16 + Turbopack → confirmado\n- D-031 DB: Postgres + pgvector → confirmado\n- D-032 LLM: OpenAI + Minimax → refinar: AI Gateway (provider/opus-4-6, sonnet-4-6) + Minimax como provider secundário\n- D-033 Realtime SSE vs WebSocket → SSE wins\n- D-034 Auth: JWT próprio vs Supabase vs Clerk → Supabase (já tem @supabase/ssr)\n- D-035 Payments: Stripe → confirmado (BRL)\n- D-036 Deploy: VPS vs Vercel vs edge → Vercel Fluid Compute\n\nVou pesquisar rapidly:\n- Vercel AI Gateway (de session start hook)\n- next-intl 2026\n- Mantine Mandala viz\n- Supabase auth best practices 2026\n- next-pwa vs Serwist 2026\n\nMas a regra é evitar WebSearch excessivo. Tenho informação suficiente de session start hooks + knowledge. Vou escrever o doc.\n\nVou verificar:\n- ID de feature_list.json R-025 para marcar passes\n- Tom de documentos anteriores (synthesis_v1, persona_v1, ux_v1)","signature":"15d7284daad838268fc0b82dd8f78c9dac4ab8f05a60627f525eef3d535efc93"}],"mode